HEADWORD: Salso-acid
<hw>Sal"so-ac`id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>salsus</ets> salted, salt + <ets>acidus</ets> acid.]</ety>
<def>Having a taste compounded of saltness and acidity; both salt and
acid.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

